revision.text:
{{no footnotes|date=September 2011}}
The '''Ayarmaca''' are an [[ethnic group]] located northwest of [[Cuzco]] in the area of modern [[Maras, Peru|Maras]]. The Ayarmaca were subjugated by the [[Inca]] during their earliest period of state expansion, ca. AD 1300. After losing their power under Inca rule, the Ayarmaca people were resettled in various communities in the Cuzco region.
