=== Premise ===
In the aftermath of the events of ''Ground Zeroes'' and the destruction of [[List of characters in the Metal Gear series#Outer Heaven|Militaires Sans Frontières]] (commonly abbreviated as MSF), [[Big Boss (Metal Gear)|Big Boss]] ([[Kiefer Sutherland]]/[[Akio Ōtsuka]]) falls into a coma.<ref>{{cite web|last=Ishaan|title=Metal Gear Solid V Trailer Is Ground Zeroes + The Phantom Pain|url=http://www.siliconera.com/2013/03/27/metal-gear-solid-v-trailer-is-ground-zeroes-the-phantom-pain/|publisher=Siliconera|accessdate=2 April 2013}}</ref> Nine years later, he awakens and helps lead a new mercenary group, [[List of characters in the Metal Gear series#Diamond Dogs|Diamond Dogs]].<ref>{{cite web|author=Rich Stanton |url=https://www.theguardian.com/technology/2015/dec/17/metal-gear-solid-games-creator-hideo-kojima-konami |title=Whatever happened to Metal Gear Solid games creator Hideo Kojima? &#124; Technology |publisher=The Guardian |date=2015-12-16 |accessdate=2015-12-22}}</ref> Adopting the codename "[[Venom Snake]]", he ventures into [[Afghanistan]] during the [[Soviet–Afghan War|Soviet-Afghan War]] and the [[Angola]]&mdash;[[Zaire]] border region during the [[Angolan Civil War]] to track down the men responsible for MSF's destruction. Along the way, he becomes reacquainted with his former rival [[Revolver Ocelot|Ocelot]] ([[Troy Baker]]/[[Satoshi Mikami]]) and encounters [[Quiet (Metal Gear)|Quiet]] ([[Stefanie Joosten]]), an assassin and sniper with supernatural abilities. While he and [[List of characters in the Metal Gear series#Master Miller|Kazuhira Miller]] ([[Robin Atkin Downes]]/[[Tomokazu Sugita]]) are initially driven to exact revenge, Snake soon unearths a plot by the [[Patriots (Metal Gear)|Patriots organization]] to develop a new model of the [[Metal Gear (weapon)|Metal Gear]] system known as the ST-84 "Sahelanthropus".<ref>{{cite journal |last=Wales |first=Matt |title=Metal Gear Solid 5 - Sahelanthropus boss fight and how to beat the final mission |url=http://www.eurogamer.net/articles/2017-10-02-metal-gear-solid-5-the-phantom-pain-skull-face-okb-zero-gates-sneaking-suit-4014?page=2 |date=March 10, 2017 |access-date=December 29, 2017 |journal=[[Eurogamer]]}}</ref>

=== Characters ===
{{see also|List of characters in the Metal Gear series}}
In contrast to previous ''Metal Gear'' installments, Kojima Productions conducted the [[voice acting]] and [[motion capture]] with English-speaking actors and stuntmen first. While [[facial motion capture|facial capturing]] was used before for ''Metal Gear Solid 4'', it was done separately from the actual voice acting. The Japanese voice acting was dubbed over the English cast's performance afterward, in contrast to previous releases in the series since ''Metal Gear Solid 2'', which had the characters' vocal and facial expressions lip-synched specifically to both, Japanese and English voice acting.

